@Grant
1) I guess my first paragraph here was a little ambiguous. I mentioned "pia maters" and "irises" because both were used in Sunday's puzzle: PIA MATERS was ugly because a) no one--not even medical professionals--would likely use that word in the plural and b) if they did, the Latin plural would be "piae matres." OTOH, people talk about bunches of more than one IRIS all the time, and even I would not be so pompous as to say "a bouquet of irides" (except in jest), although that would the Greek/Latin plural. I think you might find "irides"--referring to the anatomical parts of the eyes--used in formal scientific writing, although I doubt even that happens much any more.

2)I have never heard "Somm," either, and that, among others, held me up in the NW corner for quite a while.

